com.yworks.yfiles.view

Interface IVisibilityTestable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArcEdgeStyleRenderer, BevelNodeStyleRenderer, CollapsibleNodeStyleDecoratorRenderer, DefaultLabelStyleRenderer, DefaultPortCandidateDescriptor, GeneralPathNodeStyleRenderer, IconLabelStyleRenderer, ImageNodeStyleRenderer, MemoryImageNodeStyleRenderer, PanelNodeStyleRenderer, PathBasedEdgeStyleRenderer, PolylineEdgeStyleRenderer, ShapeNodeStyleRenderer, ShinyPlateNodeStyleRenderer, TableNodeStyleRenderer, TemplateLabelStyleRenderer, TemplateNodeStyleRenderer, TemplatePortStyleRenderer

    public interface IVisibilityTestable
    Interface that is implemented for elements that can determine whether they might be visible in a given clipping rectangle.
    See Also:
    IVisualCreator, CanvasControl, ICanvasObjectDescriptor, ICanvasObject, VisibilityTestables

    • Method Detail

      • isVisible

        boolean isVisible(ICanvasContext context,
                  RectD rectangle)
        Determines whether an element might intersect the visible region for a given context.

        Conservative implementations can always return true.

        Parameters:
        context - The context to determine the visibility for.
        rectangle - The visible region clip.
        Returns:
        false if and only if it is safe not to paint the element because it would not affect the given clipping region.
